<HEAD>Brazil Congress Says No To Casinos</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRASILIA, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Congress has rejected a
constitutional amendment to bring back casino gambling to Latin
America's largest nation.
   The vote, on Thursday, was 271-118 in favor, with 14
abstentions, but it fell nine short of the majority needed to pass
a constitutional amendment.
   Casinos were outlawed in Brazil by presidential decree in 1946.
   The Congress is sitting as a constitutional convention to
rewrite Brazil's military-dictated constitution.
