<HEAD>Safety Council: More Than 400 May Die In Holiday Accidents</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   From 400 to 500 people may die in traffic
accidents during the Independence Day holiday weekend, according to
the National Safety Council.
   The council also estimated Thursday that an additional 19,000 to
24,000 people may suffer disabling injuries from traffic accidents.
   During last year's July 4th holiday weekend, 390 people were
killed.
   Safety Council statisticians said 400 deaths might be expected
during a three-day, non-holiday weekend at this time of the year.
   This year's three-day holiday weekend begins at 6 p.m. today and
ends midnight local time Monday.
