<HEAD>Police Say More Protest Facilities Could Endanger Security</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Atlanta police officials are urging the courts
not to expand facilities for demonstrators during next month's
Democratic National Convention.
   Police said Thursday it would confound security plans for the
event.
   An umbrella dissident group, Alternative '88, is suing the city
of Atlanta in U.S. District Court for additional space for protests
near The Omni, the site of the July 18-21 convention.
   The city has leased two parking lots, covering about two acres,
