<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Obit-Volk     07-01 0096</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Obit-Volk,0099</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>West German Cardinal Volk Dies After a Lengthy Illness</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MAINZ, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Cardinal Hermann Volk, the former
Roman Catholic bishop of Mainz and an advocate of ecumenism, died
today following a lengthy illness, his press office said. He was 84.
   Volk, who served as Bishop of Mainz from 1962-82, was known for
his efforts to build ties between the Catholic and Protestant
churches. Pope Paul VI named him a cardinal in 1973.
   Volk was born Dec. 27, 1903 in Steinheim am Main.
   Funeral services will be held July 4 in Mainz.
</TEXT>
