<HEAD>Colombian Army Destroys 5 Tons of Cocaine</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOGOTA, Colombia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Army troops found and destroyed 5.2 tons
of cocaine and 36{ tons of coca leaves and paste, the Ministry of
Defense said Friday.
   The troops had been sent to a zone near Ayapel, north of Bogota,
in a search and destroy mission, the ministry said.
   Army troops and air force fighters forced the landing of two
planes in a clandestine airstrip at a farm and found more than a
ton of cocaine.
   The soldiers found another 4.2 tons of cocaine at the farm June
25, arrested two people, and confiscated sophisticated weapons and
chemicals used to process the drug.
   The VII army brigade said Thursday that in another operation in
the eastern Guaviare jungle, the military confiscated 36{ tons of
coca leaves and coca paste, the military said.
