<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BRF--FreewaySpills     07-01 0138</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Freeway Spills,0142</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Paint and Wallboard Build Freeway Mess</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   All they needed were nails and maybe
motorists could have done something constructive during the Friday
morning commute.
   Just before 7 a.m. a tanker truck was involved in a multivehicle
collision, spilling white latex paint across the westbound lanes,
divider and an eastbound lane of the San Bernardino Freeway.
   A little later a truck dropped 74,000 pounds of wallboard on the
northbound Pasadena Freeway.
   The paint spill in Baldwin Park was expected to shut down that
freeway at least until noon, said California Highway Patrol Officer
Mike Maas.
   The tanker driver suffered moderate injuries, Maas said.
   Two of the Pasadena Freeway's northbound lanes were blocked when
two trailers loaded with plasterboard overturned about 8:15 a.m.,
said CHP spokesman Dwight McDonald. There were no injuries.
</TEXT>
