<FILEID>AP-NR-07-01-88 2000EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Japan-Jobs     07-01 0144</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Japan-Jobs,0148</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Japan's Unemployment Rate Hits 37-Month Low</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rapid economic growth pushed Japan's unemployment
rate down in May to its lowest level in 37 months, while the number
of job holders hit a record 61.06 million, the government announced
Friday.
   Unemployment in May fell 0.1 percentage point from April to a
seasonally adjusted 2.5 percent, the Management and Coordination
Agency said. It represented a sharp turnaround from the record high
rate of 3.2 percent registered in May 1987.
   Officials said the 61.06 million workers was up 1.3 million from
May 1987.
   It was the greatest annual increase since November 1973, when
the number of jobs grew by 1.35 million.
   Led by strong domestic economic demand, Japan's economy grew
during the first three months of this year at a 11.3 percent annual
rate, its fastest rate of growth in 11 years.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
