<1ST_LINE>u a AM-BuildingCollapse 1stLd-Writethru a0740 07-01 0268</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Building Collapse, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0740,0272</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Two Girls Killed, One Hurt When Part of NYC Building Collapses</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES throughout with authorities now saying dead and
injured were all girls; quote from mayor on apparent cause; other
detail. No pickup. ADDS byline.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By VIRGINIA BYRNE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The front stoop and archway of a Manhattan
apartment building collapsed Friday, killing two girls and
seriously injuring a third, authorities said.
   The bodies of two girls, one 10 and the other 11, were recovered
by rescue workers, according to Lt. Mitchell Stern of Emergency
Medical Services.
   A 13-year-old girl was in critical but stable condition with
multiple trauma, said John Clark, administrator on duty at Bellevue
Hospital.
   The accident occurred at 3:10 p.m. when decayed ironwork
supporting a granite facade and a staircase gave way, officials
said.
   ``They had rotted over the years _ they're 100 years old _ and
they had not been adequately maintained and they rusted,'' said
Mayor Edward I. Koch who visited the scene Friday evening.
   ``I heard a thud and there was some smoke rising up,'' said Bob
Shapiro, 30, an emergency technician who lives across the street.
   ``There were hands reaching out of the rubble. There were hands
of a little girl. We were removing the rubble and the next thing I
knew the police were right behind us,'' said Shapiro.
   One elderly woman complained of chest pains when she and about
60 other people were evacuated from the building. She received
medical treatment at the scene.
   The names of the victims were withheld pending notification of
relatives.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
