<1ST_LINE>r f PM-TreasuryBills     07-01 0098</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Treasury Bills,0102</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Yields Fall on 52-Week Treasury Bills</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Interest rates on 52-week Treasury bills fell
in the government's latest auction to the lowest level since May.
   The Treasury Department sold $9 billion of the bills at an
average discount rate of 7.04 percent on Thursday, down from 7.08
percent at the last comparable auction on June 2.
   The rates were the lowest since May 5, when the one-year bills
sold for 6.74 percent. The new discount rate understates the actual
return to investors _ 7.54 percent with a $10,000 bill selling for
$9,288.20.
</TEXT>
