.03 to 154.50. At the American Stock Exchange, the market value
index was up .05 at 309.30.
   On Thursday the Dow Jones industrial average rose 19.73 to
2,141.71. The average finished the first half of the year with a
gain of 202.88 points, or 10.46 percent.
   Advancing issues outnumbered declines by nearly 3 to 1 on the
NYSE, with 1,177 up, 410 down and 382 unchanged. Big Board volume
came to 227.41 million shares, against 159.59 million in the
previous session.
