<HEAD>London Shares End Slightly Higher</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: RECASTS throughout to UPDATE with later activity; No pickup</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices rose fractionally Friday on the
London Stock Exchange as the market plodded along in the absence of
any market-affecting news.
   The start of the weekend and Monday's Independence Day holiday
in the United States kept many participants sidelined. In addition,
some players were taking a wait-and-see attitude amid speculation
that British interest rates could rise over the next week.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index closed 0.6
point, or 0.03 percent, higher at 1,858.2.
   On Wall Street, the Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was down
6.22 points at 2,135.49 as the London session drew to a close,
after opening about 3 points higher. Dealers said Wall Street was
not providing a substantial influence on London share prces.
   Fears of another increase in British interest rates, following
Tuesday's half-percentage-point rise to 9.5 percent in bank's base
lending rates, were triggered by renewed strength in the dollar,
dealers said.
